        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'd try creating a couple different magelo profiles for int and HP gear and compare the mana it lists. I faced much the same decision recently and haven't had reason to regret going with HP over int. I dropped a few int but overall came out with more mana (main upgrades were mana/hp earrings, neck and HP rings). Pure mana pool aside, I found the added HP significantly increased my over all mana availability and efficiency, in a way adding a few int never did. </P><P>For comparison, below is a link to my profile as currently equipped, and one with int items in the neck and ear slots rather than the HP/mana ones. The overall mana difference is small, but the HP gains are significant. </P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=277392" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=277392</a></P><P>Keep an eye out for sickly glowing orbs in the bazaar too, I've seen  a few of these really cheap, and 60 HP, 5 STA in range is pretty nice.</P><P><BR>Edited by - Nvasir on 09/06/2002  04:50:54</P><P>Edited by - Nvasir on 09/06/2002  05:13:37<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
