        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         My hardest decision was also to drop my INT for HP.  The moment came right after I purchased a Sickly Glowing Orb.  I traded it for my Dustscryer's Crystal Ball.</P><P>Here is a list of how I DUMPED my INT for HP:</P><P>Sickly Glowing Orb > Dustscryer's Crystal Ball<BR>Spider Fur Belt > Crystaline Silk Belt<BR>Electrum BS Earrings > Golden Sapphire Earrings<BR>Velium BS Necklace > Velium Sapphire Necklace</P><P>Still waiting for find something to trade for my ugly Mogguk.  Probably will be a Rokyls Channeling Crystal.  (WOOT 10INT for 50hp ANY DAY OF THE WEEK!  Plus 50mana so it sorta makes up for it!)</P><P>Also its funny when a cleric casts a heal on you and say, "You have a LOT of HP for a caster!"</P><P>Still waiting to get my Elder Wolf Hide, Froggy Robe, maybe Crystal Spider Eyes, then I should be complete and ready to RAID.  Oh the Shadel Bandit and Djarns Amethyst are great rings as well.  Cost a LOT though on my server 3k-4k for shadel, djarns I've only seen once for like 5k.</P><P>Deedrok Out.</P><P><strong>Deedrok - Level 45<BR>  Necromancer of E'ci<BR>  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234678" target="_blank">My Gear</a></strong><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
