        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=67706&amp;TOPIC_ID=7945&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=HP+vs+INT+%26+upgrades&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Although I am in the minority, I will say mana > resists > int > hp </P><P>I went the HP route for a long time.  At level 50 I had over 1400 hp self buffed. But I'm finding more and more that post 50, especially with the new changes to the game, resists are very very important.  </P><P>it's fairly smart to keep your int around 200ish so you have a respectable mana pool, but when fighting caster NPCs it doesn't matter how many HP you have, if you're getting nuked for 200-700+ it'll dissapear damn quick.  I'm currently in the process of sacraficing int and hp for resists, looking to get magic, cold, and fire in the 100-130 range while keeping int 190-200.  As far as I'm concerned HP can go hang till I'm uber enough to get some decent high level gear.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
