        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I knew people would disagree with me and that's ok.  I just know from experience that going pure HP gear has it's plus side, but it does not replace mana or resists.</P><P>We are an int caster, there's no such thing as a HP caster that's just silly.  Yes, I totally understand why you said that and to a point you are correct.  But At level 54, I'm just finding that HP are secondary to resists.  I am a fairly cautious player, and I stay out of melee range almost in every scenario.  I am always always always much more concerned about taking range damage by DOT's or Nukes than I am about refilling my mana pool or taking melee damage.</P><P>Again this is my RECENT experience talking, I too used to be a slave to the HP gear and I thought it was great, I'm simply changing my perspective due to changing hunting environments.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
