        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I think what you are seeing is definately because of the new mobs you are killing.  Almost all of the time I am solo exping I kill melee mobs.  I would probably drop some HPs for resists also if I was fighting casters for a living, but for your normal necro you most likely are better off with HPs.  </P><P>I was running at ~250 int and 1100 hps buffed at 54.  Over the last two months or so I have started decreasing my int and going with HPs.  I have noticed a definate enhancement since I started this.  I'm only down to 225 int now, but HPs are up around 1500.  My HPs stay much higher now while liching and I know I can take a few hits if the mob gets loose from fear or something.  I know this has saved my arse more than once in the last few weeks and the ability to use BoD only once every other mob is a big benifit when it's now needed to kill the mob.  This saves on my mana to boot.</P><P>Caster mobs..  Ya, put on the resists but if you dan't have any HPs it won't matter if you are at 50% health and you get only take half damage from IC.  You're still dead.  In the case of casters I would proably go HP>Resists>Int   </P><P>As long as you have HPs, you have mana.</P><P>-DV</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137300 "> <font size=-1 color=red>Darkvane</a></font> * 55 Dark Elf <a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com">Defiler</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
